    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nWhen I run `nvim --server \"$NVIM\" --remote-ui` inside a `:terminal` buffer, there's a bunch of output (which looks like the currently set statusline) that scrolls past, followed by the current tab freezing. This is because `--remote-ui` being used from inside nvim creates a loop.\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n1. `$ nvim -u NONE`\r\n2. `:terminal`\r\n3. `(in :terminal) $ nvim -u NONE --server \"$NVIM\" --remote-ui`\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nNothing should happen, or an error should be displayed and `nvim` should refuse to start up.\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\n0.9.1\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nnot applicable\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nnixos unstable, fedora 38\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nfoot\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nfoot\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nnixpkgs, fedora 38 repository",
